<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}-{y}=-{37}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{5}{y}={29}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+-{1}{y}=-{37}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{37}-{\left(-{1}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{37}-{\left(-{1}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{\left(\frac{{-{37}-{\left(-{1}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}\right)}+{5}{y}={29}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{9}}{{7}}\cdot{\left(-{37}\right)}--\frac{{9}}{{7}}{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}+{5}{y}={29}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{47.571428571429}-{\left(-{1.2857142857143}\right)}{y}+{5}{y}={29}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1.2857142857143}{y}+{\left({5}\right)}{y}={29}-{47.571428571429}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1.2857142857143}{y}+{\left({5}\right)}{y}=-{18.571428571429}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1.2857142857143}+{\left({5}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{18.571428571429}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3.7142857142857}{y}=-{18.571428571429}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{18.571428571429}}{{3.7142857142857}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+-{1}{\left(-{5}\right)}=-{37}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{\left({5}\right)}=-{37}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{37}-{\left({5}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{42}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

